.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAd%20tech%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Netflix%20has%20built%20its%20own%20in-house%20tech%20to%20facilitate%20ad%20buying%20and%20rolled%20out%20new%20sports%20programming%20that's%20popular%20with%20advertisers.%20Bringing%20adtech%20in-house%20can%20be%20complicated%2C%20though%2C%20and%20analysts%20will%20be%20looking%20for%20detail%20on%20Netflix's%20progress%20as%20it's%20weaned%20itself%20off%20Microsoft's%20Xandr%20to%20sell%20ads%20using%20partners%20such%20as%20The%20Trade%20Desk%20and%20Google's%20DV360.%20One%20question%20is%20whether%20Netflix%20has%20attracted%20any%20new%20advertisers%20this%20way%2C%20Raymond%20James%20analysts%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20related%20question%20is%20how%20much%20room%20is%20left%20to%20grow%20in%20the%20ad%20tier.%20Since%20launching%20in%202022%2C%20it%20has%20ramped%20up%20quickly%20by%20offering%20people%20a%20lower-priced%20option%20as%20it%20raised%20the%20price%20on%20ad-free%20versions%20and%20cracked%20down%20on%20password%20sharing.%20By%20November%2C%20the%20company%20said%2C%20it%20had%20reached%2070%20million%20global%20users.%20In%20January%2C%20it%20said%20that%20the%20ad%20plan%20made%20up%20over%2055%25%20of%20new%20sign-ups%20in%20countries%20where%20it's%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECreator%20content%20and%20sports%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Analysts%20want%20to%20hear%20more%20about%20Netflix's%20plans%20for%20sports%20programming%2C%20with%20its%20associated%20ad%20appeal.%20They're%20also%20interested%20in%20what%20execs%20have%20to%20say%20about%20plans%20to%20build%20out%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetflixs-ceo-says-its-better-for-creators-than-youtube-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecreator-driven%20content%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20YouTube%20increasingly%20dominates%20TV%20viewership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20increases%20the%20opportunity%20and%20necessity%20around%20advertising%2