s%2C%20the%20judge%20could%20also%20step%20in%20%26quot%3Bin%20the%20interest%20of%20justice%26quot%3B%20and%20appoint%20an%20outside%20council.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20significantly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E's%20pardon%20power%20would%20enable%20him%20to%20void%20any%20prosecution%20or%20its%20consequences%2C%20legal%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYes%2C%20the%20president's%20pardon%20power%20does%20reach%20criminal%20contempt%20prosecutions%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Margaret%20Love%2C%20a%20clemency%20attorney%20and%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Justice%20pardon%20attorney%20between%201990%20and%201997.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20in%20fact%2C%20his%20very%20first%20pardon%20during%20his%20first%20term%20in%20office%20was%20issued%20in%20a%20criminal%20contempt%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20Love%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20former%20Arizona%20sheriff%20Joe%20Arpaio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-pardons-joe-arpaio-2017-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArpaio%20was%20pardoned%20in%202017%20%3C%2Fa%3Eafter%20being%20found%20guilty%20of%20criminal%20contempt%20for%20violating%20a%202011%20court%20order%20in%20a%20racial%20profiling%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWednesday's%20decision%20by%20Boasberg%2C%20who%20sits%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20found%20that%20there%20was%20probable%20cause%20to%20find%20the%20Trump%20administration%20exhibited%20%26quot%3Bwillful%20disobedience%20of%20judicial%20orders%26quot%3B%20for%20ignoring%20his%20order%20from%20last%20month%20to%20immediately%20turn%20around%20planes%20full%20of%20deportees%20headed%20to%20an%20El%20Salvador%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration%20has%20argued%20it%20did%20not%20violate%20the%20judge's%20orders%20because%20the%20planes%20had%20already%20left%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20vacated%20Boasberg's%20order%20blocking%20the%20deportation%20and%20said%20Texas%2C%20not%20DC%2C%20has%20jurisdiction%20over%20deciding%20if%20the%20federal%20Alien%20Enemies%20Act%20was%20properly%20applied%20in%20removing%20the%20deportees%20from%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20that%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20excuse%20the%20Government's%20violation%2C%26quot%3B%20Boasberg%20wrote%20Wednesday%2C%20in%20pursuing%20a%20possible%20contempt%20conviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoasberg%20in%20his%20opinion%20offered%20several%20steps%20before%20contempt%20would%20be%20prosecuted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20the%20administration%20could%20seek%20to%20remedy%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bpurge%26quot%3B%20the%20violation%20of%20the%20judge's%20order%2C%20including%20by%20recognizing%20that%20the%20White%20House%20retains%20some%20control%20over%20what%20happens%20to%20the%20deportees%2C%20something%20Trump%20has%20so%20far%20denied.%20The%20deportees%20could%20then%20challenge%20their%20detentions%20in%20a%20US%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20administration%20could%20also%20suggest%20its%20own%20remedy%2C%20the%20judge%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20administration%20instead%20does%20nothing%2C%20the%20judge%20would%20begin%20the%20contempt%20process%20by%20determining%20which%20administration%20official%20or%20attorney%20is%20%26quot%3Bresponsible%26quot%3B%20for%20violating%20the%20turn-around%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20government%20failed%20to%20assist%20in%20naming%20who%20is%20responsible%2C%20the%20judge%20would%20make%20a%20determination%20after%20holding%20more%20hearings%20and%20seeking%20input%20from%20the%20detainees'%20attorneys%2C%20the%20judge%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20next%20step%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20wrote%2C%20would%20be%20for%20the%20court%20to%20%26quot%3Brequest%20that%20the%20contempt%20be%20prosecuted%20by%20an%20attorney%20for%20the%20government.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20Government%20'declines'%20or%20'the%20interest%20of%20justice%20requires%2C'%20the%20Court%20will%20'appoint%20another%20attorney%20to%20prosecute%20the%20contempt%2C'%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20wrote%2C%20quoting%20from%20federal%20criminal%20procedure%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20precedents%20for%20a%20presidential%20pardons%20in%20criminal%20contempt%20cases%20stretch%20back%20centuries%2C%20said%20Frank%20Bowman%2C%20an%20emeritus%20professor%20of%20criminal%20and%20constitutional%20law%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Missouri%20School%20of%20Law.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%20arguments%20when%20Arpaio%20was%20pardoned%2C%20saying%20that%20to%20do%20so%20would%20invalidate%20the%20separation%20of%20powers%2C%26quot%3B%20Bowman%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20truth%20is%20that%20the%20precedent%20for%20these%20pardons%20is%20so%20powerful%2C%20going%20back%20over%20the%20past%20two%20centuries.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Boasberg%20no%20longer%20has%20jurisdiction%20over%20the%20case%2C%20he%20can%20only%20pursue%20contempt%20for%20an%20administration%20official%20or%20lawyer's%20past%20conduct%20in%20his%20courtroom%2C%20Bowman%20said.%20If%20someone%20is%20found%20in%20contempt%20and%20then%20pardoned%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20would%20be%20the%20end%20of%20the%20ballgame%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20professor%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20spokesman%20Steven%20Cheung%20said%20the%20administration%20will%20appeal%20Boasberg's%20finding.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BThe%20President%20is%20100%25%20committed%20to%20ensuring%20that%20terrorists%20and%20criminal%20illegal%20migrants%20are%20no%20longer%20a%20threat%20to%20Americans%20and%20their%20communities%20across%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Cheung%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20story%20has%20been%20updated%20to%20include%20additional%20expert%20comment.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftr